com.raweng.built

Class BuiltObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.raweng.built.BuiltObject
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    BuiltInstallation, BuiltRole, BuiltUser

    public class BuiltObject
extends java.lang.Object
    BuiltObject is used to create, update and delete built object on the Built.io Backend server.
    Author:
    raw engineering, Inc

      • getAllObjects

        public java.util.ArrayList<BuiltObject> getAllObjects(java.lang.String key,
                                             java.lang.String classUid)
        Get value for the given reference key.
        Parameters:
        key - key of a reference field.
        classUid - class uid.
        Returns:
        ArrayList of BuiltObject instances. Also specified classUid value will be set as class uid for all BuiltObject instance.

        Example :
          //'blt5d4sample2633b' is a dummy Application API key
  // Assuming 'projectObject' is a BuiltObject instance
  //'bltf50esamplefeb' is uid of an object of 'comment' class

 BuiltApplication application = Built.application(context, "blt5d4sample2633b");
 BuiltQuery commentQuery      = application.classWithUid("comment").query();

 ArrayList<String> arrayList = new ArrayList<String>();
 arrayList.add("for_task");

 commentQuery.includeReference(arrayList);

 commentQuery.execInBackground(new QueryResultsCallBack() {

      @Override
      public void onCompletion(ResponseType responseType, QueryResult builtqueryresult, BuiltError builtError) {

              if(builtError == null){

                 List<BuiltObject> list = builtqueryresult.getResultObjects();
                  for (int i = 0; i < list.size(); i++) {
                           BuiltObject   taskObject = list.get(i);
                           BuiltLocation location = taskObject.getAllObjects("for_task", "task");
                  }
              }
      }
 });

      • upsert

        public BuiltObject upsert(java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> value)
        To update/insert value.
        Parameters:
        value - HashMap object containing key value pair on which search is performed and if an existing object is found containing those pair(s), it is updated else a new object is created(when the object is saved).
        Returns:
        BuiltObject object, so you can chain this call.

        Example :
             //'blt5d4sample2633b' is a dummy Application API key
     //Assuming 'projectObject' is a BuiltObject instance
     BuiltObject projectObject = Built.application(context, "blt5d4sample2633b").classWithUid("project").object();

     HashMap searchCriteria = new HashMap();
     searchCriteria.put("name", "Super Project #41!");

     HashMap replaceCriteria = new HashMap();
     replaceCriteria.put("name", "Super Project #42!");

     projectObject.upsert(searchCriteria);
     projectObject.set(replaceCriteria);

      • on

        public void on(Built.EventType eventType,
      com.raweng.built.BuiltOnEventCallback callback)
        This function registers an event listener.
        [Only avaliable with realtime]
        Parameters:
        eventType - event name.
        callback - BuiltOnEventCallback object to notify the application when the request has completed.

        Given below is the list of supported events.

        Create [Work with BuiltClass.object()]:- The 'create' event is triggered when a new object is created in the BuiltClass with which the BuiltObject constructor is associated. Registered callback is invoked with the created object.

        Update :- Update event is triggered when any/uid_specific object in the BuiltClass with which the BuiltObject constructor is associated is modified. Registered callback is invoked with the updated object.

        Delete :- Delete event is triggered when any/uid_specific object in the BuiltClass with which the BuiltObject constructor is associated is deleted. Registered callback is invoked with the deleted object.

        Broadcast :- Broadcast event is triggered when a message is broadcast for objects belonging to a particular class. Registered callback is invoked with the broadcast message.



        Example :
         //'blt5d4sample2633b' is a dummy Application API key
 BuiltApplication builtApplication = Built.application(context, "blt5d4sample2633b");
 BuiltClass projectClass   = builtApplication.classWithUid("project");
 BuiltObject projectObject = projectClass.object();
        
 //for example we are using EventType.CREATE.
 projectObject.on(Built.EventType.CREATE, new BuiltOnEventCallback() {
        
      @Override
      public void onReceive(Object object, BuiltError error) {

      }
        
 });
